-- Monsoon in India Was 16 Percent Below Normal in June, Weather Bureau Says
-- Thomas Kutty Abraham
-- 2010-07-01T02:29:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/monsoon-in-india-was-16-percent-below-normal-in-june-weather-bureau-says.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, was 16 percent
below average last month, the weather office said.  
 The nation received 137.5 millimeters of rain in June,
comapred with the 50-year average of 163.5 millimeters, the
India Meteorological Department said on its website. The monsoon
is stalled since June 18 and may revive in the next two days,
the bureau said.  
